    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.00/2–1654: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_ATC1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Achilles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-16T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 16, 1954—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2974. Repeated information Saigon 324, Berlin 247. Berlin for <gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss>. Foreign Office official stated today: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>Although Berlin conference may end without agreement being reached on
                            meeting with Communist China at Geneva in April, fact that US, Great
                            Britain and France have agreed in principle on eventual discussion
                            Indochina problem with Communist China provides <persName
                                corresp="#p_BG1">Bidault</persName> with a sufficiently strong
                            position to marshal support for continued exploration this line at
                            Paris. Pursuance this line also permits unhurried approach problem
                            negotiation and thus provides needed time to improve French Union
                            military position Indochina and strengthen Vietnamese national
                            army.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Jacquet, as reflected in recent press articles, has proposed to
                            Council of Ministers elimination office Commissioner General for
                            Indochina on basis it serves no useful purpose and French representation
                            accredited individual states sufficient. However, this personal view
                            Jacquet and impossible as yet tell what <persName corresp="#p_BG1"
                                >Bidault</persName>’s and <persName corresp="#p_PR1"
                                >Pleven</persName>’s views will be this regard.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_ATC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Achilles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
